6 ‚Äì Manipulating Data: Loops
Sometimes we need to repeat the same operation for all elements of a vector, or all rows/columns of a matrix. This is called a loop.

apply, sapply, lapply
apply() repeats an operation over all rows or columns of a matrix or data frame. The second argument controls whether rows (1) or columns (2) are used:

#| '!! shinylive warning !!': |
#|   shinylive does not work in self-contained HTML documents.
#|   Please set `embed-resources: false` in your metadata.
#| standalone: true
#| viewerHeight: 300
library(shiny)
CHUNK_ID &lt;- "w1_c21"
